body:
Markiplier June 24th Highlights

Talked a lot about how filming in Texas for 2 months had a lot of bugs (due to lights), snakes, spiders.

Info about the Big Project (which had a crew of 30 people and should hopefully come out in October/November):

  • Had to shoot some scenes at night in the woods
  • Filmed at night in an empty field in the woods
  • “Not tropical but more lush in the forest-scape” location
  • Dressed in shorts and a cutoff tee covered in makeup/dirt
  • Another Youtuber in that scene who has less clothes (male)
  • No nudity
  • Shooting in a pit, lighting from the top, in a forest surrounding
  • Another location where it was wooded shooting day and night at a decommissioned suage plant shut down in 2006
  • Can’t wear a mask as Mark is in front of the camera
  • Filmed in the building of the place
  • Power still worked in the plant
  • Longest filming location (a week)
  • Mentioned something about “shooting running into the (building)”

Bonus: there was a dead beaver in the sewage plant they filmed in

Closing remarks:

  • Mark wants to get back on schedule with videos by tomorrow
  • Member streams
  • Work on post production for this big project
  • Hinted at having another project planned for next year

Feel free to add any theories, remarks, etc.

blog.name: drlyana
blog.title: Just me
blog.description:
I'm a weird combination of a photographer, surgeon, psychotherapist in training, wife, new youtuber; I'm nature worshiping, old ways researching and practicing. 
Living a healthy vegan life (mostly whole foods plant based). 
Shorter said: I'm a wild, free, independent woman, connected with myself, on a path of self discovery and growth.
I don't know what my future is going to bring me, but I'm making the best of every situation.
Welcome here! Cheers!
